{"lemma":"نابَ","slug":"نابَ","root":"ن.#.ب","root_slug":"ن-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-ب","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"نُبْتَ","in_corpus":true,"count":10,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"نُبْتِ","in_corpus":true,"count":10,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"نُبْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"نُبْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"نُبْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"نابَ","in_corpus":true,"count":9,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"نابَت","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"نابا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"نابَتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"نابُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"نُبْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَنُب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَنُوب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَنُوبِي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَنُوبِينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَنُوبا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَنُوبانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَنُوبُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَنُوبُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَنُبْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَنُب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَنُوب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَنُب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَنُوب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَنُوبا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَنُوبانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَنُوبا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَنُوبانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَنُوبُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَنُوبُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَنُبْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"نُبْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"نُبْتُ","in_corpus":true,"count":10,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَنُوب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَنُوب","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":42,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40777"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to replace, to substitute"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to act on behalf of, to represent"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to nod assent to, to agree with, to turn towards"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fang, tusk","examples":[{"text":"10th century, Al-Mutanabbi\nإِذَا رَأَيْتَ نُيُوبَ ٱللَّيْثِ بَارِزَةً\nفَلَا تَظُنَّنَّ أَنَّ ٱللَّيْثَ يَبْتَسِمُ\nʔiḏā raʔayta nuyūba l-layṯi bārizatan\nfa-lā taẓunnanna ʔanna l-layṯa yabtasimu\nIf you see the lion’s fangs jut out,","english":"you are not supposed to believe that the lion smiles!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"canine tooth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"large teeth, long thick teeth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old she-camel"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"not on target"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dislikable, hideous","examples":[{"text":"كان يصرخ بشتائم نابية زلزلت جدران القسم.","english":"He exclaimed shabby insults making the walls of the department tremble."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic ניב (nīḇ, “fang, tusk; pincer”) unless otherwise a Proto-Semitic development, potentially an extension from Akkadian 𒉏𒋭 (nūbtu, “honeybee; stringers”), hence sharp things that pierce in and do not release like a predator's use of canine teeth. The sense \"aged female camel\" makes reference to the length of the female camel's permanent canine teeth, which begin to emerge around 7 years of age. It belongs morphologically to the root ن ي ب (n y b), with connections to نُوب (nūb, “bees”), Ugaritic 𐎐𐎁𐎚 (nbt, “honey”), Phoenician 𐤍𐤐𐤕 (npt, “virgin honey”), Ge'ez ንህብ (nəhb, “bee, drone”), and Shehri nibbet (“bee, wasp, stinging insect”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of نَبَا (nabā, “to be or go amiss”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40777","headword_ar":"نَابٌ","root":"nyb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayabN","text_ar":"نَيَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canine tooth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog-tooth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye-tooth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tusk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tush;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fang;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of certain animals:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the teeth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tooth that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaAEiyap","text_ar":"رَبَاعِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next but one to the central pair of incisors:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K.) [In this sense, the word is masc.:] the tooth thus called is mase., when thus called: [though if you call it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is fem.:] but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"when fem. signifies “ an old she-camel ” (Msb:) or, accord. to the M and K, it is fem. only in each of the above senses without distinction. (TA.) Sb says, that the Arabs observed the pronunciation termed imáleh ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAlap","text_ar":"اـِمَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the nom. [as well as in the acc. and gen., in which latter case this pronunciation is agreeable with analogy on account of the final kesreh,] likening its (tropical:)  to that in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaY","text_ar":"رَمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in which it is expressed in writing by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] because it is changed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is extr. That is, this pronunciation of (tropical:)  changed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is only observed [regularly] when the said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a final radical letter; and specially in verbs: the instances of this kind that occur in nouns are extr.; and more so are those in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a medial radical letter. (TA.) [But the restriction to the case of verbs is inconsistent with what is said by Ibn-Málik and other high authorities: and so, too, is the restriction to the case of a final radical letter.] Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyubN","text_ar":"اَنْيُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both pls. of pauc.: but the latter is used as a pl. of mult.:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyuwbN","text_ar":"نُيُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) the latter contr. to analogy, (S,) because ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbN","text_ar":"نَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayabN","text_ar":"نَيَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] a word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not [regularly] assume the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the pl.; (TA;) to which should be added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyuwbN","text_ar":"نِيُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a dial. var., as in the case of every pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which the medial radical letter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, F:) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAyiybu","text_ar":"اَنَايِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) Ibn-Seenà says that no animal has both a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a horn. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbN","text_ar":"نَابٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aged she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) not applied to a male camel: (S;) so called because of the length of her lush; (S;) by synedoche; the whole being called by the name of a part: (TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayuwbN","text_ar":"نَيُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) accord. to some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nay~awbN","text_ar":"نَيَّوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake: (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyuwbN","text_ar":"نُيُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niybN","text_ar":"نِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or these are pls. of both the former of sing. (K. accord. to some copies; and TA.) Sb is of opinion that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niybN","text_ar":"نِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":", and says that the Arabs have made it of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolN","text_ar":"فُعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as it is said to be in the S, for it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyobN","text_ar":"نُيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as they have the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", disliking the sound of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyuwbN","text_ar":"نُيُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with dammeh, and preceded by dammeh, and followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":". It is also said to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayuwbN","text_ar":"نَيُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as it is related, on the authority of Yoo, that certain of the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiydN","text_ar":"صِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyDN","text_ar":"بِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayuwdN","text_ar":"صَيُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayuwDN","text_ar":"بَيُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with the dial. of those who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rusolN","text_ar":"رُسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rusulN","text_ar":"رُسُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; namely, the tribe of Temeem but their not saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyubN","text_ar":"نُيُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuyudN","text_ar":"صُيُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuDN","text_ar":"بُيُضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is an argument in favour of the opinion of Sb. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEalu *`lika maA Han~ati Aln~iybu","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ مَا حَنَّتِ النِّيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do that as long as aged she-camels yearn towards their young ones"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., I will never do it]. A proverb. (S.) ―         -b4-  The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbN","text_ar":"نَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyayobN","text_ar":"نُيَيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":", as applied to an aged she-camel, is like an epithet: (S:) or rather this formation of the dim. without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dev. from constant rule. (MF.) Sh says, that some of the Arabs make the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwayobN","text_ar":"ثُوَيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because many an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as that in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":": [or rather, this is generally the case:] but this, says Ibn-Es-Sarráj is an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"error"},{"kind":"text","text":"on his part [who does so]. (S.) This apparently means, that Ibn-EsSarráj accuses Sh of an error; but such is not the case: for Sb himself says “ but this is an error on their part; ” i. e., on the part of the Arabs who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwyb","text_ar":"نويب"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nyyb","text_ar":"نييب"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbu qawomK","text_ar":"نَابُ قَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, of a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaAbN","text_ar":"اَنْيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~atohu A^anoyaAbu Ald~ahori","text_ar":"عَضَّتْهُ اَنْيَابُ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuyuwbuhu","text_ar":"نُيُوبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dog-teeth of fortune bit him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnyAb","text_ar":"انياب"},{"kind":"text","text":"are likewise met. assigned to evil, or mischief. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Lh","K","S","M","F","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}